# Workshop publishing

When you finish edits to **track content**, **`track_scripts/`**, **`assignment.md`**, **`scripts/`**, **`tools/`**, or anything learners pull on **`es3-api`**:

1. **Commit** to `git` (`main`) and **`git push origin HEAD`** (or the user’s working branch).
2. Run **`instruqt track validate`** then **`instruqt track push`** from the repo root.

Or run **`./scripts/push_git_and_instruqt.sh`** after committing (it does not create commits).

Learners refresh sandboxes with **`./scripts/sync_workshop_from_git.sh`**; Instruqt still needs **`instruqt track push`** for bundled/challenge assets tied to the track definition.
